CLOCK_MODE().details: Indicates that timestamps are used instead of block numbers

returns._0: A string indicating the clock mode ("mode=timestamp")

DOMAIN_SEPARATOR().details: Returns the domain separator used in the encoding of the signature for {permit}, as defined by {EIP712}.

approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `value` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

availableBalance(address).details: Returns the available (unfrozen) balance of an account.

params.account: The address to query the available balance of.

returns.available: The amount of tokens available for transfer.

balanceOfAt(address,uint256).details: Returns the balance of an account at a specific block number

params.account: The address to query the balance of
params.timepoint: The block number to query the balance at

blockUser(address).details: Only callable by addresses with USER_MANAGEMENT_ROLE

returns._0: True if user was not previously blocked

blocked(address).details: Returns the blocked status of an account.

burn(uint256).details: Destroys a `value` amount of tokens from the caller. See {ERC20-_burn}.

burnFrom(address,uint256).details: Destroys a `value` amount of tokens from `account`, deducting from the caller's allowance. See {ERC20-_burn} and {ERC20-allowance}. Requirements: - the caller must have allowance for ``accounts``'s tokens of at least `value`.

canManageYield(address).details: Only addresses with SUPPLY_MANAGEMENT_ROLE can manage yield

returns._0: True if the address has SUPPLY_MANAGEMENT_ROLE

cap().details: Returns the cap on the token's total supply.

clawback(address,address,uint256).details: Only callable by addresses with SUPPLY_MANAGEMENT_ROLE. Requires sufficient balance.

params.from: The address to take tokens from

clock().details: Overrides the default clock function to use timestamps instead of block numbers

returns._0: The current timestamp as a uint48

constructor.details: Sets up the bond with its initial configuration and grants roles to the initial owner

params._cap: The maximum total supply of the token
params._faceValue: The face value of the bond in underlying asset base units (must be > 0)
params._maturityDate: Timestamp when the bond matures (must be in the future)
params._underlyingAsset: The address of the underlying asset contract (must be a valid ERC20)
params.decimals_: The number of decimals for the token (must be <= 18)
params.forwarder: The address of the trusted forwarder for meta-transactions
params.initialOwner: The address that will receive admin rights
params.name: The token name

decimals().details: Overrides the default ERC20 decimals function to use the configurable value

freeze(address,uint256).details: Adjusts the amount of tokens frozen for a user.

params.amount: The amount of tokens frozen. Requirements: - The user must have sufficient unfrozen balance.
params.user: The address of the user whose tokens to freeze.

frozen(address).details: Returns the amount of tokens frozen for a user.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

isTrustedForwarder(address).details: Indicates whether any particular address is the trusted forwarder.

mature().details: Only callable by addresses with SUPPLY_MANAGEMENT_ROLE after maturity dateRequires sufficient underlying assets for all potential redemptions

mint(address,uint256).details: Only callable by addresses with SUPPLY_MANAGEMENT_ROLE. Emits a Transfer event.

params.amount: The quantity of tokens to create in base units
params.to: The address that will receive the minted tokens

returns._0: The amount of underlying assets missing (0 if there's enough or excess)

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

nonces(address).details: Returns the current nonce for `owner`. This value must be included whenever a signature is generated for {permit}. Every successful call to {permit} increases ``owner``'s nonce by one. This prevents a signature from being used multiple times.

pause().details: Only callable by addresses with DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE. Emits a Paused event.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

permit(address,address,uint256,uint256,u.details: Sets `value` as the allowance of `spender` over ``owner``'s tokens, given ``owner``'s signed approval. IMPORTANT: The same issues {IERC20-approve} has related to transaction ordering also apply here. Emits an {Approval} event. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `deadline` must be a timestamp in the future. - `v`, `r` and `s` must be a valid `secp256k1` signature from `owner` over the EIP712-formatted function arguments. - the signature must use ``owner``'s current nonce (see {nonces}). For more information on the signature format, see the https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-2612#specification[relevant EIP section]. CAUTION: See Security Considerations above.

redeem(uint256).details: Can be called multiple times until all bonds are redeemed

params.amount: The amount of bonds to redeem

redeemAll().details: Can only be called after the bond has matured

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

setYieldSchedule(address).details: Override this function to add additional access control if needed

params.schedule: The address of the yield schedule contract

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

topUpMissingAmount().details: Will revert if no assets are missing or if the transfer fails

topUpUnderlyingAsset(uint256).details: Anyone can top up the contract with underlying assets

params.amount: The amount of underlying assets to top up

totalSupplyAt(uint256).details: Returns the total supply at a specific block number

params.timepoint: The block number to query the total supply at

returns._0: The total amount of underlying assets needed

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `value`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Skips emitting an {Approval} event indicating an allowance update. This is not required by the ERC. See {xref-ERC20-_approve-address-address-uint256-bool-}[_approve]. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `value`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `value`.

trustedForwarder().details: Returns the address of the trusted forwarder.

unblockUser(address).details: Only callable by addresses with USER_MANAGEMENT_ROLE

returns._0: True if user was previously blocked

unpause().details: Only callable by addresses with DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE. Emits an Unpaused event.

withdrawExcessUnderlyingAssets(address).details: Only callable by addresses with SUPPLY_MANAGEMENT_ROLE

params.to: The address to send the underlying assets to

withdrawToken(address,address,uint256).details: Only callable by admin. Cannot withdraw underlying asset.

withdrawUnderlyingAsset(address,uint256).details: Only callable by addresses with SUPPLY_MANAGEMENT_ROLE

params.amount: The amount of underlying assets to withdraw
params.to: The address to send the underlying assets to

returns._0: The amount of excess underlying assets

yieldBasisPerUnit(address).details: For bonds, the yield basis is the face value

returns._0: The face value as the basis for yield calculations

yieldToken().details: For bonds, this is the underlying asset

clock().notice: Returns the current timestamp for historical balance tracking
